# Model Selection Guide

When starting a new task, briefly consider which model fits best:

## Haiku (cheapest, fastest)
- Git operations (commit, push, status)
- Simple file edits with known changes
- Adding routes, imports, menu items
- Reformatting, renaming, moving code
- Boilerplate generation
- Configuration changes

## Sonnet (default for most work)
- Feature implementation (new pages, services, components)
- Debugging and troubleshooting
- Planning and creating plans
- Writing content drafts
- Code review
- Most tasks that require reading multiple files and reasoning

## Opus (only when Sonnet isn't enough)
- Architecture decisions with significant tradeoffs
- Debugging that Sonnet failed to resolve
- Complex multi-system refactors
- High-stakes writing (investor materials, legal)
- Deep strategic analysis

## Gemini (web research, long documents)
- Tasks requiring real-time web search
- Analyzing very long documents (>100K tokens)
- Competitive research
- Fact-checking current information

If you are Haiku or Sonnet and the task clearly needs a more capable model, say so at the top of your response.
